<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880628-0153 </DOCNO><HL> Continental's MaxSaver Fare </HL><SO> </SO><CO> TEX </CO><IN> AIR </IN><DATELINE> HOUSTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Continental Airlines, a unit of Houston-based Texas Air Corp., said it is cutting the advance purchase requirement on its MaxSaver fares to seven days from 14 days.    The eased restriction is good for tickets purchased for summer and fall travel. MaxSavers are the lowest discount fares offered.    Additionally, Continental is extending the off-peak MaxSaver period to include noon through midnight on Saturdays, as well as the current period of noon Mondays through noon Thursdays. </TEXT></DOC>